WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
Oxford Bookworm's Library.

00:03.000 --> 00:05.000
Starter.

00:05.000 --> 00:08.000
The Girl with Green Eyes.

00:08.000 --> 00:10.000
By John Escott.

00:10.000 --> 00:14.000
Read by Christopher Ragland.

00:14.000 --> 00:20.000
Published and copyright, Oxford University Press 2012.

00:30.000 --> 00:38.000
The Girl with Green Eyes.

00:38.000 --> 00:45.000
Greg is a porter at the Shepton Hotel in New York.

00:45.000 --> 00:52.000
After work, he always goes for a coffee across the street.

00:52.000 --> 00:59.000
A girl is sitting in the coffee shop near the window.

00:59.000 --> 01:02.000
It's her again.

01:02.000 --> 01:04.000
Thanks Greg.

01:04.000 --> 01:08.000
She's here every afternoon.

01:08.000 --> 01:12.000
I'm going to say hello.

01:12.000 --> 01:19.000
Greg goes into the coffee shop and gets a coffee.

01:19.000 --> 01:24.000
Then he goes across to the girl's table.

01:25.000 --> 01:28.000
Hi, he says.

01:28.000 --> 01:30.000
I'm Greg.

01:30.000 --> 01:34.000
Can I sit with you?

01:34.000 --> 01:37.000
Okay, she says.

01:37.000 --> 01:41.000
I'm Cassie.

01:41.000 --> 01:48.000
I come here for a coffee every day after work, says Greg.

01:48.000 --> 01:53.000
I'm a porter at the Shepton Hotel.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
He smiles.

01:55.000 --> 02:00.000
You have beautiful green eyes.

02:00.000 --> 02:02.000
Have I?

02:02.000 --> 02:04.000
She says.

02:04.000 --> 02:08.000
She doesn't smile.

02:08.000 --> 02:11.000
Is something wrong, Cassie?

02:11.000 --> 02:13.000
He asks.

02:13.000 --> 02:18.000
You don't look very happy.

02:18.000 --> 02:21.000
It's nothing.

02:21.000 --> 02:24.000
She says.

02:24.000 --> 02:28.000
Tell me, says Greg.

02:28.000 --> 02:31.000
Maybe I can help.

02:31.000 --> 02:35.000
Well, she begins.

02:35.000 --> 02:40.000
Go on, says Greg.

02:40.000 --> 02:45.000
My stepfather is staying at the Shepton Hotel.

02:45.000 --> 02:47.000
She says.

02:47.000 --> 02:51.000
He has my sketchbooks.

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
I'm an artist.

02:54.000 --> 03:00.000
When I ask him to give them to me, he says, no.

03:00.000 --> 03:05.000
I want you to come back home to Boston.

03:05.000 --> 03:10.000
But I don't want to go back to Boston.

03:10.000 --> 03:14.000
He's not nice.

03:14.000 --> 03:21.000
How long is he going to be at the hotel, asks Greg?

03:21.000 --> 03:26.000
Two more days, says Cassie.

03:26.000 --> 03:31.000
He's in room 724.

03:31.000 --> 03:37.000
Maybe I can get the sketchbooks for you, says Greg.

03:37.000 --> 03:42.000
Maybe I can get into his room.

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
Can you?

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
She says.

03:46.000 --> 03:54.000
Meet me here tomorrow afternoon at 4.30, says Greg.

03:54.000 --> 03:56.000
Okay.

03:56.000 --> 04:00.000
Thank you, says Cassie.

04:00.000 --> 04:03.000
Thank you very much.

04:03.000 --> 04:06.000
She looks at her watch.

04:06.000 --> 04:09.000
I've got to go now.

04:09.000 --> 04:13.000
See you tomorrow.

04:13.000 --> 04:22.000
When Cassie gets back to her hotel room, she makes a telephone call.

04:22.000 --> 04:24.000
Hello?

04:24.000 --> 04:26.000
She says.

04:26.000 --> 04:28.000
It's me.

04:28.000 --> 04:30.000
It's okay.

04:30.000 --> 04:33.000
The boy's going to do it.

04:33.000 --> 04:35.000
Yes.

04:35.000 --> 04:41.000
I'm going to get them from him tomorrow afternoon.

04:41.000 --> 04:43.000
Okay.

04:43.000 --> 04:49.000
I can meet you there the morning after at 10 a.m.

04:49.000 --> 04:52.000
Don't forget to bring the money.

04:52.000 --> 04:57.000
$2,000.

04:57.000 --> 05:03.000
Next morning, Greg arrives at work early.

05:03.000 --> 05:09.000
He goes to find room 724.

05:09.000 --> 05:17.000
I have to wait for Cassie's stepfather to go out, he thinks.

05:17.000 --> 05:25.000
I don't know his name, but it doesn't matter.

05:25.000 --> 05:32.000
Greg watches the door of room 724.

05:32.000 --> 05:39.000
He sees the girl come to clean the rooms.

05:39.000 --> 05:48.000
Some minutes later, a man comes out of room 724.

05:48.000 --> 05:55.000
That must be Cassie's stepfather, thinks Greg.

05:55.000 --> 06:07.000
He waits for the man to leave, and for the cleaning girl to go into room 724.

06:07.000 --> 06:13.000
I need to look in the room, he thinks.

06:13.000 --> 06:18.000
Greg waits for the girl to leave the bedroom.

06:18.000 --> 06:27.000
Then, he goes into the room and begins to look for the sketchbooks.

06:27.000 --> 06:31.000
I must be quick, he thinks.

06:31.000 --> 06:35.000
Where are they?

06:35.000 --> 06:42.000
Suddenly, Greg sees the sketchbooks by the bed.

06:42.000 --> 06:46.000
Got them, he thinks.

06:46.000 --> 06:51.000
He begins to look at the pictures.

06:51.000 --> 06:57.000
Wow, Cassie is a great artist.

06:57.000 --> 07:01.000
These are good.

07:01.000 --> 07:09.000
Greg is leaving the room when he hears the cleaning girl call out to him.

07:09.000 --> 07:12.000
Hey, she says.

07:12.000 --> 07:15.000
What are you doing?

07:15.000 --> 07:18.000
Come back.

07:18.000 --> 07:23.000
Greg does not stop.

07:23.000 --> 07:33.000
Greg finishes work that afternoon and leaves the hotel through a door in the next street.

07:33.000 --> 07:44.000
When he gets near the front of the hotel, he sees the man from room 724.

07:44.000 --> 07:48.000
That's him again, thinks Greg.

07:48.000 --> 07:53.000
That's Cassie's stepfather.

07:53.000 --> 07:58.000
Greg waits for the man to go into the hotel.

07:58.000 --> 08:04.000
Then, he goes to the coffee shop.

08:04.000 --> 08:10.000
Cassie is at the same table in the coffee shop.

08:10.000 --> 08:17.000
Greg gets a coffee and goes to sit with her.

08:17.000 --> 08:25.000
I have them, he says, and he puts the sketchbooks on the table.

08:25.000 --> 08:30.000
That's great, says Cassie.

08:30.000 --> 08:34.000
How can I thank you, Greg?

08:34.000 --> 08:38.000
You can meet me later, he says.

08:38.000 --> 08:45.000
After I go home and change out of my Porter's uniform.

08:45.000 --> 08:50.000
I'm sorry, Greg, says Cassie.

08:50.000 --> 08:53.000
I can't tonight.

08:53.000 --> 08:57.000
Maybe tomorrow night.

08:57.000 --> 09:00.000
Okay, says Greg.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.000
Tomorrow night.

09:02.000 --> 09:07.000
We can get something to eat first.

09:07.000 --> 09:11.000
Yes, okay, says Cassie.

09:11.000 --> 09:20.000
I have to go now, but meet me here tomorrow evening at six o'clock.

09:20.000 --> 09:24.000
Cassie gets up, ready to leave.

09:24.000 --> 09:29.000
Don't forget your key, says Greg.

09:29.000 --> 09:35.000
Oh, thanks, says Cassie.

09:35.000 --> 09:39.000
She takes it from him quickly.

09:39.000 --> 09:42.000
See you tomorrow.

09:42.000 --> 09:49.000
Greg is finishing his coffee when he sees his friend, Mike.

09:50.000 --> 09:55.000
You're in trouble, Greg, says Mike.

09:55.000 --> 10:00.000
Jake Russo's sketchbooks are not in his room.

10:00.000 --> 10:04.000
Room 724.

10:04.000 --> 10:12.000
And there are CCTV pictures of you coming from that room.

10:12.000 --> 10:17.000
Who is Jake Russo?

10:17.000 --> 10:20.000
asks Greg.

10:20.000 --> 10:25.000
Suddenly, he's not feeling very well.

10:25.000 --> 10:29.000
An artist, says Mike.

10:29.000 --> 10:34.000
His pictures sell for thousands of dollars.

10:34.000 --> 10:39.000
And his sketchbooks sell for thousands too.

10:39.000 --> 10:42.000
Do you have them?

10:42.000 --> 10:44.000
asks Mike.

10:44.000 --> 10:51.000
No, a girl has them, says Greg.

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
What girl?

10:53.000 --> 10:55.000
asks Mike.

10:55.000 --> 11:00.000
A girl with green eyes, says Greg.

11:00.000 --> 11:06.000
And he tells Mike about Cassie and her stepfather.

11:07.000 --> 11:14.000
But it's not true, says Mike, when Greg finishes speaking.

11:14.000 --> 11:21.000
Jake Russo doesn't have a wife or a stepdaughter.

11:21.000 --> 11:27.000
You have to find that girl and get the sketchbooks, Greg.

11:27.000 --> 11:33.000
And you have to do it before the police find you.

11:33.000 --> 11:39.000
Greg walks home to his one room apartment.

11:39.000 --> 11:43.000
How am I going to find her?

11:43.000 --> 11:45.000
He thinks.

11:45.000 --> 11:55.000
She has Jake Russo's sketchbooks now, so she's not going to meet me again.

11:55.000 --> 12:01.000
Is she going to sell them for a lot of money?

12:02.000 --> 12:10.000
There is a police car in the street, next to Greg's apartment.

12:10.000 --> 12:15.000
Oh no, he thinks.

12:15.000 --> 12:18.000
They're waiting for me.

12:18.000 --> 12:24.000
I can't get into my apartment now.

12:24.000 --> 12:31.000
That night, Greg sleeps on a train in the subway.

12:31.000 --> 12:34.000
But early the next morning,

12:34.000 --> 12:39.000
Hey you, says a man.

12:39.000 --> 12:42.000
He's the subway cleaner.

12:42.000 --> 12:44.000
Get up.

12:44.000 --> 12:49.000
You can't sleep here all day.

12:49.000 --> 12:54.000
Sorry, says Greg.

12:54.000 --> 13:00.000
People are arriving to get their trains now.

13:00.000 --> 13:07.000
One of them stops and looks at a photograph in his newspaper,

13:07.000 --> 13:11.000
and then at Greg.

13:11.000 --> 13:16.000
It's him, thinks the man.

13:16.000 --> 13:22.000
It's the young man in the newspaper photograph.

13:22.000 --> 13:27.000
The police are looking for him.

13:27.000 --> 13:34.000
Suddenly, Greg sees the man looking at him,

13:34.000 --> 13:41.000
and he sees his picture on the front of the man's newspaper.

13:42.000 --> 13:46.000
I have to get out of here quickly.

13:46.000 --> 13:49.000
He thinks.

13:49.000 --> 13:55.000
The man with the newspaper finds a policeman.

13:55.000 --> 13:57.000
It's him.

13:57.000 --> 14:01.000
He tells the policeman.

14:01.000 --> 14:05.000
The hotel porter.

14:05.000 --> 14:08.000
Hey, you.

14:08.000 --> 14:12.000
The policeman calls to Greg.

14:12.000 --> 14:16.000
Greg runs.

14:16.000 --> 14:18.000
Stop!

14:18.000 --> 14:21.000
Calls the policeman.

14:21.000 --> 14:25.000
Greg doesn't stop.

14:25.000 --> 14:32.000
I have to get out of this uniform, thinks Greg.

14:32.000 --> 14:37.000
People know I'm the porter.

14:37.000 --> 14:44.000
Maybe Mike can give me something different to wear.

14:44.000 --> 14:51.000
When he gets to Mike's apartment, Mike opens the door.

14:51.000 --> 14:54.000
I need something to wear.

14:54.000 --> 14:57.000
Greg tells him.

14:57.000 --> 15:02.000
I can't go back to my apartment.

15:02.000 --> 15:11.000
I have pictures in the newspaper, and yes, I know, says Mike.

15:11.000 --> 15:14.000
It's okay.

15:14.000 --> 15:17.000
Come in.

15:17.000 --> 15:21.000
Way as the girl asks Mike.

15:21.000 --> 15:24.000
Do you know?

15:24.000 --> 15:28.000
No, says Greg.

15:28.000 --> 15:32.000
What can you remember about her?

15:32.000 --> 15:34.000
Says Mike.

15:34.000 --> 15:39.000
There must be something to help you find her.

15:39.000 --> 15:44.000
Yes, Greg says suddenly.

15:44.000 --> 15:47.000
Her key.

15:47.000 --> 15:53.000
A key to a room in the Dolphin Hotel.

15:53.000 --> 16:00.000
It's a small, cheap hotel near 42nd Street.

16:00.000 --> 16:04.000
She must be staying there.

16:04.000 --> 16:07.000
What's the time?

16:07.000 --> 16:13.000
Nearly nine o'clock, says Mike.

16:13.000 --> 16:18.000
Maybe she's there now, says Greg.

16:18.000 --> 16:22.000
I have to go.

16:22.000 --> 16:26.000
Thanks, Mike.

16:26.000 --> 16:33.000
Twenty minutes later, Greg is near the Dolphin Hotel.

16:33.000 --> 16:36.000
Am I too late?

16:36.000 --> 16:39.000
He thinks?

16:39.000 --> 16:46.000
Suddenly, Greg sees Cassie come out of the hotel.

16:46.000 --> 16:50.000
Cassie, he calls.

16:50.000 --> 16:52.000
Wait.

16:52.000 --> 16:57.000
I have to talk to you.

16:57.000 --> 17:03.000
Cassie sees him, but she doesn't stop.

17:03.000 --> 17:08.000
There is a car waiting for her.

17:08.000 --> 17:16.000
She says something to the driver and gets into it quickly.

17:16.000 --> 17:21.000
Oh, no, says Greg.

17:21.000 --> 17:26.000
Here, 83.

17:26.000 --> 17:30.000
Says an old man in the street.

17:30.000 --> 17:34.000
Greg looks at him.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.000
What?

17:36.000 --> 17:53.000
The girl is going to peer 83 West 42nd Street for the circle line boat.

17:53.000 --> 17:56.000
Says the old man.

17:56.000 --> 17:59.000
Greg smiles.

17:59.000 --> 18:03.000
Thanks, he says.

18:03.000 --> 18:07.000
And he begins to run.

18:07.000 --> 18:15.000
Greg runs all the way to peer 83.

18:15.000 --> 18:24.000
People are getting on to the boat, and he gets a ticket.

18:24.000 --> 18:30.000
On the boat, Greg looks for Cassie.

18:30.000 --> 18:36.000
But a woman with a newspaper is looking at him.

18:36.000 --> 18:40.000
It's the young man in the picture.

18:40.000 --> 18:43.000
She tells the man with her.

18:43.000 --> 18:48.000
Call the police, Eddie.

18:48.000 --> 18:55.000
The man gets his phone and calls the police.

18:55.000 --> 19:01.000
Some time later, Greg sees Cassie.

19:01.000 --> 19:05.000
She is talking to a man.

19:05.000 --> 19:13.000
But Greg does not see two policemen get on the boat.

19:13.000 --> 19:17.000
They quickly find Greg.

19:17.000 --> 19:22.000
Where are Jake Russo's sketchbooks?

19:22.000 --> 19:26.000
The first policeman asks him.

19:26.000 --> 19:32.000
I don't have them, says Greg.

19:32.000 --> 19:35.000
You don't want me.

19:35.000 --> 19:38.000
You want her.

19:38.000 --> 19:43.000
She has the sketchbooks.

19:43.000 --> 19:46.000
Hey, look.

19:46.000 --> 19:48.000
He's right.

19:48.000 --> 19:52.000
Says the second policeman.

19:52.000 --> 19:59.000
The two policemen move quickly to Cassie and the man.

19:59.000 --> 20:05.000
I don't understand, says Cassie.

20:05.000 --> 20:07.000
How?

20:07.000 --> 20:15.000
The two of you are coming with us, says one of the policemen.

20:15.000 --> 20:19.000
You're in trouble.

20:19.000 --> 20:28.000
Later, Greg and a policeman take the sketchbooks back to the hotel.

20:28.000 --> 20:35.000
Jake Russo is very happy to see them again.

20:35.000 --> 20:44.000
I'm sorry, Mr. Russo, says Greg, and tells him everything.

20:44.000 --> 20:51.000
It's okay, says the artist, smiling.

20:51.000 --> 20:59.000
But stay away from girls with beautiful green eyes.

